text: A new favorite spot in East Las Vegas where the selection is unique, not just the fish tacos but all the food we have tried & we ate quite a variety and it was ALL delicious, their special hibiscus water is dynamite & the service is outstanding "especially from Erica"!!!

I've heard a lot of good things about this place and finally decided to pull the trigger, and was so glad I did! It's a Cute little place with some of the best, most unique mexican-style food I've had. The salsa is addictive and seriously spicy, but so delicious! The woman who waited on us was very friendly and helpful! The restaurant had a very comfortable and relaxing atmosphere, and I also want to note how nice the bathrooms were. For anyone looking for something different, this is the place to go! My only regret is not visiting sooner!!Overall a really great experience and I definitely plan on returning!
Un lugar super agradable! La comida deliciosa,  me encantó! ! Simplemente DELICIOSO!!
The food is sooo good. I had a chicken gordita and shrimp taco with chipolte cream sauce. Service and presentation just as good. This place is a keeper.
Ericka, our server was very welcoming and the food her is delish.. Two thumbs up, for sure!!
This place was amazing..well priced..and very clean..I got the lunch special with a fish and chips taco and the el fish taco..it was the best ever...I highly recommend this restaurant

The best customer service ever!! Our waitress was very attentive, offered explanations of their various dishes, attentive to the free refills of horchata and jamaica water. Every dish we tried was excellent! Their specialty was my favorite- "la Costra" which you can choose from various options. I had the shrimp and fish. We are definitely coming here again on this same trip in Vegas. The presentation and service was more than expected for their very budget friendly menu!
This place is a fun little spot with amazing food.  The dishes are packed with flavor and are presented creatively.

I'm so glad I dropped in to try this delicious gem of a resturant . Amazing service and even better food . I came with my dad who is usually never please with any place we eat at and he's already planning when we will come again ! So happy such a yummy place opened in my neighborhood.
Just came in for a quick bite & ended up w/ a meal to die for!! No regrets tho.  Loved the cleanliness & awesome customer service.  Definitely coming back
This place was SO good! The fish tacos, steak burrito and ceviche were outstanding .. We also ordered chips & salsa & guacamole. Everything tasted so fresh and it was all really good prices!

First thing you notice walking into the place is the colorful, yet nautical look! There is inside seating, as well as outside seating. 

As for the food, it's so tasty. They start you with a taster of their shrimp juice and lime. We had he Poblano taco & the "Al pastor" fish costra. The Poblano has fish, chile rajas tossed witb corn and semi creamy sauce! The Fish costra was a flour tortilla fish taco, but the fish is wrapped in a grilled cheese wrap with chipotle salsa. We also had the Shrimp Burrito (exactly what it sounds like) and it was tasty! 

Note: Definitely buy a Groupon, it can get a bit pricey! (4 stars for price, but seafood is fresh!)

Omg, what a hidden jem! ! Warm service and amazing food. Seven seas soup was loaded with seafood and so good. Lobster contras were like nothing I've tried before, delicious. Sorry I didn't post pics, we wolfed down the food before anyone could remember to snap some pics. I'll post next time, like tomorrow...

I have anxiously awaited the opening of this Restaurant for quite some time. Yesterday I had the opportunity to indulge that wait. The staff was very friendly.
The menu extensive. I chose the Octopus tostada and was happily surprised.
Very refreshing expertly prepared. I give this quality restaurant 5 Stars. I shall
return often to explore that vast menu.

A friend and I recently had lunch at my new favorite Las Vegas eatery - El Fish Taco! This is not your average "taco joint". This is a fabulous little restaurant that serves amazingly different and unique food. The Octopus taco is excellent, as is the Ahi Tuna tostada. Everything is fresh, yummy, and reasonably priced.
Do yourself a favor and check this place out. It's on Tropicana, just east of Eastern. It's clearly a "Mom & Pop" place, so let's give them some business. You'll be glad you did!
Love this restaurant!  Fresh seafood & the salsas are delicious! The staff is very nice.... We've been there a few times & everything has been great!

We ate lunch at El Fish Taco in November.  It's a wonderful restaurant.  There were three of us and we tried five different types of tacos.  We loved all the tacos.  We also order the guacamole (good) and chips, and a crepe for desert.  The crepe was unbelievably good.

Our waitress was great.  She had a wonderful attitude, and provided prompt and courteous service.  Convenient location.  You gotta try this place.

He ido seguido a comer aquí todo lo que he probado esta delicioso, el servicio muy bueno y súper limpio, muy buen ambiente muy agradable ya nos hacia falta en Las Vegas algo así, original y muy rico, y los precios súper accesibles.EXCELENTE !!
This place is the amazing. Best Mexican restaurant I ever have. I wish there is the same one is California. By the way, we will come back this restaurant every time we travel to Las Vegas.

ABSOLUTELY FANTASTIC! I was in Las Vegas on business and I don't like to eat at the "tourist" style food stops on the strip. I had the Shrimp El Fish Taco Costra and the El Fish Taco. Both were obviously made fresh and were absolutely delicious! The staff was extremely nice and the food was outstanding! I would highly recommend a visit when in the Las Vegas area!
Don't bother eating anywhere else in Vegas.  Try the Surf and Turf Costa it's life changing. Erika will never steer u wrong.

Awesome, not your average fish taco place, after eating here you won't be saying, let's blow this taco stand ! You will be coming back for more.
If you appreciate good service good quality at a great price, its for you.

Very good experience first time. So many different things to choose from make this a very unique place. Don't let the location and outside appearance bother you. Very nice decor and clean inside. Service was great and waiter was very helpful with recommendations. The chips are fantastic. Shrimp ceviche was phenomenal. Shrimp costra was fantastic. Bacon taco was just ok and didn't have much bacon flavor. Fish and chips taco was also just ok. Many other things on the menu to try next time. We will definitely be back

Wow!!! Que buena comida!! Un concepto diferente de buena calidad y muuuuuuy delicioso!!! Dense la oportunidad de deleitar todos sus sentidos, y tienen un plus, te atienden con amabilidad, calidad y calidez te hacen sentir apreciado como cliente, por favor no vengan en busca de porquerías grasosas, insisto, ESTO ES COMIDA DE CALIDAD y a un precio bastante razonable, hoy probé un postre que se llama PANACOTA!!!! OMG!!! se van a enamorar, animense a probar no se van arrepentir; algo para subrayar el lugar es hermoso, esta limpio y su musica es muy agradable y nada estridente.

Great food! Nice atmosphere. Very friendly and professional staff. I had the Pastor, Poblano, Camaron y chorizo and tostada do ceviche. This is a "must try" place. I will be back next time I'm in Vegas!

Passed by this place many times and finally had a chance to check it out. It was pretty good and the food tasted very fresh. Of course, I had a fish taco, a battered one, which I enjoyed. Since I was cold, I tried the lobster bisque. That was also very good with nice chunks of lobster in it. Then, last I decided to try something new: the Angus steak costra. It was this grilled cheese stuffed with steak placed in a soft corn tortilla, like a taco. It's kind of hard to explain. The waitress said the owner is from Mexico City and that costras are popular there. I did like it.
This place was a 10! Service was great, food was delicious and it was all very reasonabley priced.  I could (and want to) eat here every day.

Really like this place! Is a diferent and good option  too the already busy taco business in that area.the costras are  my favorite thing here never had them before! Costras are tacos but your " guisado" or what ever you taco ingredient are the wrapped the in a fabulous layer of grill melty cheese and then the put it in a tortilla. So good.
Food and service at its best!!! Will frequent this place! So happy they are down the street from work!

We have passed this place many times and wanted to check it out so when we found a groupon for them we decided to check them out. The places is small but nicely decorated and very clean. The waitress was very friendly and provided good feedback when we had questions on what something was or how she liked it. She was very attentive and pleasant. I am guessing the guy frequenting the tables was the owner he was very nice asking everyone if they enjoyed their meal, if it was their first time, and invited them to return when they were leaving. This place oozes hospitality! The food was just as good as the service, it was served hot, fresh and in a timely manner. I really love their food it's different from most taco places they have this volcano toco that has the meat of your choice fried cheese on top and this tasty sauce on top, my husband couldn't stop raving about the Tortilla soup with shrimp in it. To finish off the meal I ordered the Nutella crepes which were yummy I just wish the Nutella taste was a little more present in the dish I tasted more chocolate with a hint of the hazelnut flavor I love so much! But it was delicious either way The guy I am assuming the owner advised when I return  to try the Carmel one which is made with Mexican Carmel. The only thing I would change about this place is to replace can soda's for a soda machine.
Everything tastes very fresh and exploding with flavors and drinks are tasty too!  Customer for life.
Food is great if you are looking for a seafood tacos this is the place to go .... And to add to that the service is very good :)

Surprised: Clean, new, upscale-looking fish taco place in a run down area. Limited menu with a variety of tostadas, tacos, burritos, and some lobster options. Served a shiny silver cup of complimentary seafood soup, tasty!

Confused: Despite the name, menu has a few tostadas but only two tacos, neither of which are actually fish tacos. Both contain shrimp? At least you get to specify your preference of corn or flour tortillas.

Impressed: The octopus tostada is beautiful! Gorgeous shreds of bright purple cabbage, plentiful chopped octopus, bright green avocado slices, and a drizzle of mojo mayo! Taste was fresh, not too acidic, large portion for the price.

Disappointed: The tacos, both shrimp, were just okay. One had grilled peppers and onions, the other had black beans and rice. Shrimp itself was bland. Considering tacos are their namesake dish, they need more of them on the menu and better flavor. For starters, grill your shrimp.

Satisfied (with service): Minor issue with billing, charged $5.50 for a taco listed as $3.50 on the menu. Pointed it out to friendly male server, who apologized and refunded the difference cash promptly. Check your receipt to be on the safe side.

Went on Sunday. Only one table was busy. 4 tables where dirty so it limited the place where I could seat with my family. The table I sat on was still dirty. The food was good. Got a plate with some tostadas for my ceviche and it was dirty asked to have it changed. None of the tables  where cleaned since I got there and left. The food is good but they need more attention on cleaning. Never got the broth they always give.

Over priced. I ordered fish tacos & fish were basically just thrown on the grill & cooked it that's it.  No seasoned or anything. I have to put salt &a pepper, lots salsa on my tacos or taste very plain.  My server was very nice but we totally ignored by owner.  He went other tables how they were doing but he never came our table to checked on us.  Well, I could made better tacos my own anyway.  Won't go back there.

This place is awesome! Super friendly staff and wonderful food! I had the el fish taco and the governor,  the governor was a little bland but the el fish was beyond delicious!  The tortilla soup with shrimp is a MUST, along with their chips and salsa! 
Go check this place out!
Went there on Tues Nov. 24. the food was awesome! Had the Shrimp soup Then the Ahi Tuna Tostado. do not miss this place, its food is as good as any on the strip. but not strip prices

My boyfriend and I had El Fish Taco bookmarked since we saw all of its great reviews and for our love of tacos. We were excited when we finally came in. We were expecting the typical taqueria, but it's actually a casual sit-down restaurant. Once you walk in, they allow you to select your own seating, then they come to you with the menus. Woah, the menu is priceeeyyy! The tacos are $3+ EACH omg. lol I mean, they do have some interesting/bizzare tacos you wont find really anywhere else, but its still pretty pricey. I opted for the Surf & Turf Taco, and since many people on Yelp enjoy their "Costras" I also ordered the Al Pastor Shrimp Costra. What's a Costra? It's like a melted grilled cheese taco with your choice of meat. It was decent. The two didn't fill me up so I also ordered the Fish & Chips Taco. (I ordered tacos I thought were interesting). My boyfriend got the Chipotle Shrimp Burrito. Everything tasted good, but they definitely are not worth the price.. Tbh, I would rather opt for a cheaper joint with good tacos.. if they drop their prices to typical prices, we may come back, but we both agreed its just too much for okay food

Tried this place once and it was alright. The place is really cute, can be easily located from the street, plenty of parking spaces. We were there at a slow time, we were the only table and they only had one guy working. Service was a little slow considering we were the only table. 

We got the Seafood nachos which was good. Nice portion, crispy tortilla, nice amount of seafood... pretty presentation. 

We also tried the El Fish Taco (their signature I'm assuming) this was alright.. actually kind of bland. Baja taco which was alright, Poblano Taco which was the best of the ones we tried. 

For dessert we tried the Pana Cotta which was really good. I could have eaten the cream alone without the fruit on top.. the fruity sauce was actually really sour. 

The nachos and dessert were really good, but for a place that specializes in fish tacos, the fish tacos were not very good.
Excellent service.  Nice menu variety. Excellent guacamole.  Good salsas. Loved the El Fish Taco.  Hibiscus water flavorful and pretty. Good quality. Nice serving presentation.

Absolutely incredible,  this is such a hidden gem! ! The service was quite incredible, the food was outstanding!   The owner and staff were very personable making the experience perfect!  The owner recommended the "Costra  Lobster Tacos " which were out of this world!  They grill cheese and wrap it around the meat and put it in a warm tortilla with their signature sauce!  Best thing is the value of their menu is affordable and delicious! ! Very thankful I stumbled apon this place and look forward to our future visits!

What a nice little gem! I had chips and guacamole which by the way tasted homemade and was really fresh. The fish taco was good. They brought out a shrimp soup which if you are a fan of shrimp you will love. A bit spicy though so be ready. The chicken tacquitos.... AMAZEBALLS! All in all great service.

Got a groupon for this restaurant and was really impressed. We went after lunch so it was slow but I loved the feel of this place. The food is the true star here though. You kinda have to love sea food, that is what most of their menu consists of. The owner was there and was able to explain the menu to me and my husband. They have homemade Mexican horchata and Jamaica, both pare fabulous! One of the stars of the meal was the side of beans. I know.... Beans? But really they are to die for! Don't pass them up. Other than that order what looks good because you honestly can't go wrong. I'm so happy that Groupon led me there because I will definitely be back. They also started serving alcohol now and will be having a Valentines special. So stop reading and head on over!
Great ceviche and mixed seafood cocktail.  I love the freshness.  Gotta try the hibiscus water made fresh. Staff was very friendly.  Homemade cheladas with modelo.  Bilingual staff.

As far as fish tacos go, el fish taco doesn't get any better! They are creative and have a number of seafood combination options. It's obvious they value unique flavors as well as plate presentation. You would think for the price that you would pay twice as much. My only complaint was I walked away too full to finish my delicious dulce de leche crepes! I met the owner Mario who stopped to personally greet me and crack a few jokes. Thanks el fish taco!

Not from Vegas but was driving thru. Was just going to grab something on the strip, but decided to give this a try. Blown away. Best fish tacos I've ever had....the el fish taco was excellent. Poblano was great. I didn't try the costras but my dad did. He said "best food in Vegas". 

Do try something with the chipotle sauce. It's great. 

Service was also excellent.

I love this place! The atmosphere is cool, the food presentation is very powerful and the food is fantastic! I was expecting a regular taco shop, but this is gourmet in every aspect except the price. The servixe, the plating and the food is top notch and the place is just fun to be at. I highly recommend the homemade horchata, and check the specials board for great items that aren't on the menu! I highly recommend El Fish Taco!

You have to give this place a try.  It's different than anything else in town, in a good way.  If you love seafood there is a great selection... If not, they have other meats.  They don't skimp on the chunks of lobster, octopus, etc.  Excellent service and atmosphere too!

Excellent the best im from Mexico Tijuana Bc they have one of the best fish tacos octopus lobster etc  this one is the closest the jicama taco tamarindo ,gobernador , and lobster taco are amazing everything me and my husband love coming here also the dessert crepas with cream cheese delicious highly recommended !!!!

Holy COW! AMAZING!  Found it completely by mistake via Grubhub.  We couldn't choose so ordered way to much food and ate every bite! No pics because we ate too darned fast amazed at every bite!!!  Queso Chicheron (fried cheese the size of an "american Mexican salad" bowl, Lobster Thermidor Taco (OMG I want BOTTLES of the sauce on this), Mixed Cocktail (Shrimp and Octopus) Shrimp Tortilla Soup, Pork Gordita, um... Other stuff... Every bite has been tender, delicious, perfect!!!! Will be back again and again and again!!!!  And Again!  Love love love!

Everything we had was delicious and well prepared. Each taco comes with the matching salsa especially prepared for the dish. Carpas with langosta amazing. 


The crepe with cajeta was great ! 

*the music was in Spanish and it was soft rock pop*

The price of the food was great. I got the governors Taco, and shrimp volcano,  and the al pastor taco. Def was full after all of it. The tortillas are home made and the beans actually taste like my mom makes them. 
Not too busy for a saturday night. The place was pretty open, youre not sitting all up in everyones business.

Be forewarned this is primarily a sit-down restaurant.  I ordered the "El Fish Taco" from the menu with shrimp for carry out since I was on my work lunch. Was brought a little silver cup of what I thought was sauce, but also received plastic cups of sauces when my taco arrived.  1 tiny baby taco with 3 shrimp, a slice of avocado, and some beans & rice showed up even though the menu only showed pairs of tacos. Was given my bill in a padded cc portfolio like a higher end restaurant would do and was told they would take it when ready. ???  1 tiny shrimp taco is $4.32 incl. tax.  I just left a 5. The taste was alright, nothing out of this world. I have to say seeing El Pollo Loco across the parking lot on the way to my car with my baby taco almost brought a tear to my eye. Lol

Amazing fish tacos 
I don't know what the costras are , but the are F@&ibg amazing 
Big thumbs up

Great restaurant!! The Custer service is amazing. The aguachile was too spicy for me, and the waiter noticed and asked me if I wanted it changed. The food was delicious and unique. It wasn't too much food, and everything was amazing.

Stopped in to see if the posted reviews were legit or just a lot of puffing for this new business;  fortunately, everything met or exceeded my expectations!

Our table ordered the chips and salsa(s), steak burrito, fried chicken taquitos, chicken gordita platter and angus steak tacos and ALL were FIRST RATE DISHES!!!! 

Outside of the absence of a crowd, this visit was a 5 star experience; friendly service, pleasing ambiance, high end presentation and great food! Best of all, this is a family operated business and their food is about as authentic as it gets!

If you like good authentic cooking and no crowds (at least for now) don't miss this one!

I wish I could give it more stars...staff is passionate about their food and their service is excellent...can't even describe how delicious the food is. Seafood is extremely fresh, you can taste that tortillas are homemade and their horchata is fresh made.

A few weeks ago I was driving West on Trop looking for a quick taco place and saw El Fish so I decided to stop in. Since then I have taken three different groups of people to this restaurant, recommended someone to go here, ordered different food each time, and so far I have not been burned and always been blown away by the experience. The food and service is really good here. The wait staff is so friendly and nice and it is fun to chat with the owner who is sometimes sitting in the dining area. I usually start with chips and salsa, but if you like fresh guac - go for the chips and guac - it is amazing.  I go for two different tacos every time. The angus beef is my favorite, but everything is really good. Do not leave without trying the crepes. I normally don't eat desert at lunch, but the experience here was so good, I had to try and I was not disappointed. This has become my go-to place for lunch and for lunch meetings. It is easy to find, good parking and good location. I would love to give it five stars, but I wish the seating was a little more comfortable. I sat at one of the higher tables on my last visit and it was more comfortable than the booth, so go with that.

Found this spot while browsing through yelp, trying to find some place with really good fish tacos. Everything looked amazing in the pics and my bf and I are into trying new things. It was pretty good. Some things were more of a feast upon your eyes. It wasn't bad though. It was just alright right.  I would recommend it as a place to try if you want to try something different. Just once.
The shrimp el fish tacos or off the hook love coming here. The customer service is on point they're on top of it and always come to check and see how everything is and if you need anything.
Amazing food,  relax,  great service!!!!!  Definitely coming back again!!!!  Everything is fresh!!  I really recommend this place!!!!

Regresamos al Fish Taco, la primera vez la comida estaba bueno pero ahora sigue mas buena todavía. Este restaurante se ha esforzado en ofrecer comida de primera calidad a buen precio.
El Fish Taco, la costra, El Poblano delicioso! Para los que no comen mucho marisco también tienen en el Menú: Gorditas, tacos de Asada entre otros.
Servicio excelente y el lugar siempre esta limpio.

Five stars and not because I'm losing my mind or feeling charitable.  El Fish Taco brings fine dining flavor and quality at street fair prices.  The restaurant is a refreshing break from most Latino eateries that serve the same list of items.  Every dish at El Fish is an original creation.

All items are a'la'carte.  So, you can make yourself as stuffed with yummy goodness as you like. Every single item down to the tortillas are made fresh daily on the premises.  

My only complaint is that once people find out about this place, I won't be able to get a seat.

Totally surprised! NOT your typical greasy taco spot! So fresh and yummy.. Hand made tortillas, need I say more! I had a fish taco and a shrimp tostada.. Flavorful fresh and delicious! The salsas were good.. Just the right amount of heat. Refreshing horchata and Jamaica drinks not overly sweet like many other Mexican restaurants taste like they make that in house too.. Overall great experience will definitely bring my family back!
Amazing octopus tostadas. Lots of variety for seafood or meat tacos.  Not your typical Mexican.   Great service. Erika our waitress was wonderful.

WOW...  El Magnifico!!!

Best new place I've experienced in years...  Staff was very courteous & friendly.   

The food was very very good, fresh & delivered exactly shown on the menu...  Which I've never experienced.

The staff was attentive but never overly intruding!  

A must experience for yourself.... We'll be driving back again from Summerlin to this great find on Yelp!!!
Authentic tacos at this place.  Gorditas were good also.  Chicharron, Fish, Chorizo and Shrimp was all good.

Amazing, fantastic, wonderful. I can't express how great this small restaurant is.
As a tourist this wasn't the first place to try but the signage is what caught our attention. 
The food is great, the service is great, and this is the place to go!
Great sea food grilled plate, very fresh seafood, for $16 you get a mixture of grilled fish, chipotle chicken and very tender octopus with 3 sides

Fish and chips burrito is a dense bit of goodness. Guac and chips is a favorite; ask them for lightly salted chips, though, as they go a bit salt overboard. The lobster tacos did not have a lot of flavor, but the fish and shrimp tacos and costra were great. The nachos were fantastic, as was my horchata.

It's a great little restaurant. Lots of windows but stays very comfortable even on the coldest days.

The folks running the place are kind and attentive.

I'd recommend they keep the audio down a bit more, as it tends to be too loud for the space; I'm sure they would have turned it down if I had asked, but I did not ask.

If interested in a quick snack, I heartily recommend their guac and chips for takeout. Best I've had.
Stopped in for a fish and chip burrito.  It didn't click in my mind the a taco joint would refer to French fries for chips.  It worked pretty well.  I'll be back to try other items.

El Fish Taco is a taco, burrito, tostada restaurant located in East-ish Las Vegas by McCarran and UNLV. They advertise their seafood dishes a la "fish" tacos and their agua frescas aka fresh waters like Jamaica and Horchata.

They have a $4.99 two taco and fresh water lunch special that my best friend has been raving about. I stopped in for dinner to a mostly empty restaurant. I think it's super cute. The cuteness even overflowed into the presentation of the food. They have baskets with different hot sauces in them on the tables, a wood plank theme, and outside seating. They had one server working whom also did hostess duties, and presumably some kitchen work.

The prices are very fair. They have unique items, the food is fresh, and the space is updated. Most of the tacos were $3.50-$4.50 depending on the ingredients used. Having a couple would definitely satisfy a light lunch or dinner.

The complimentary fish soup comes out in a metal shot glass with a handle and tastes delicious with a squirt of lime to give it some freshness.

The food came out on a wooden plank/tray with the tacos on holders. I believe the tortillas were house made by the way they looked: rustic and imperfectly round. 

The food was good with the tostado being my favorite. It was topped with a cream sauce and loaded with a diced octopus, onion, and citrus mixture. The poblano taco had grilled fish, corn, and poblano peppers. The other taco was spicy with chorizo, potato, and shrimp. The shrimp was a little over cooked so the flavors were a little muddled but I still enjoyed it.

With a horchata my total was close to $15. For 4 items I say that's not bad at all.

Would I return? Yes. The price is right, they have captivated my taste buds to try the whole menu, and the food was good. I can't say much about service because I didn't need much. They set a cute pitcher on the table and napkins were in the basket so I was pretty easy to deal with. With that said the lady working was pleasant.

My one negative was the horchata. It had an unfamiliar floral flavor to it that was off putting. I didn't even drink half of the small cup. Being a first timer it would have been nice if they explained which salsas to eat the tacos with, as they served a red and green salsa next to my tacos. Aside from those two things I listed I can't give them a five because there was a some wow factor missing from the food. It was good but not amazing.

We stopped here by chance as we were leaving Vegas on a Sunday. It was a great stop for lunch and we will be adding it to our list of places to hit up off-strip. We ordered the surf and turf Cortas by recommendation of the server.  Also got a fish taco and an octopus taco. Octopus was cooked very well and nicely seasoned. Service was great too. I tried a Poblano chili and potato gordita, and it was also very good. I did think the chilies were very spicy in that dish, but attributed to luck of the chili draw. Definitely recommend giving this place a chance. They do tacos right.

This place is yum! The location is kind of hard to get to right now, with all the construction,  but it's worth the effort! The ambience is casual, with lots of windows so it's nice and bright. You get a complimentary shot of the shrimp consomme with lime! The place is called El Fish Taco, and appropriately they've got a ton of seafood options, but if you're not in the mood,  they have steak options too. I love how there are so many other variations on the seafood taco than just fried fish filet and shrimp. 

I had the al pastor fish taco,  shrimp taco,  and poblano fish taco my first visit, and the steak costra the second time. Everything came out quickly and was delicious! In terms of dessert, there's not much in the way of traditional Mexican dishes,  but they have crepes and panna cotta. I love cajeta, so the dulce de leche crepe was right up my alley. Coming back for sure.
The best fish taco ever! I really love to get quality food with an exotic Mexican soul flavor. This place  endorse a Real Baja food restaurant. Love it!!
Easily overlooked hidden gem for Mexican seafood. Eat here, you won't regret it. Oh, and try the horchata!

I'll start off by saying that I've never stepped foot into the actual restaurant.

However, I have ordered from El Fish Taco through GrubHub several times. The process is easy and the food always arrives before expected. :)

My boyfriend is obsessed with the shrimp ceviche, it is probably his favorite thing there. I always order the shrimp tacos, they're my absolute favorite! 

This place is seriously great. Prices are fair. Fast delivery. They never mess up the delivery either. And the food always arrives hot. 

Thank you for the great service.

Service, food, and ambience are all 5 stars! I ordered the fish and chips taco, lobster thermidor taco, and the el fish taco costra. All 3 were amazing. Fish and shrimp was fresh - juicy, not rubbery. I'll definitely be coming back!!

MY GOD THIS PLACE IS AMAZING!!

I ordered the shrimp burrito, shrimp ceviche and horchata to go. While I waited, I was given some shrimp soup in the cutest little bowl and while I was initially hesitant to try it, after one sip I downed it like it was my first drink on a hot summers day! So good! When I returned home with my food and took that first bite of the burrito, literal ecstasy inside my mouth. The burrito was overloaded with shrimp, so much so that I made little tacos out of the remainders with the tortillas provided. The ceviche!! So mouthwatering and delicious! The right amount of seasonings, shrimp and cucumbers. I barely used the crackers provided and just simply inhaled it with a fork. All the food was AMAZEBALLS! Definitely recommend!!

First time trying it out today. The wife and I were both impressed with the food. Simple and elegant. Prices are affordable. Laid back atmosphere. The wife had the fish n chips burrito and I had al pastor costra. Planning on making this a regular spot for us

Food is amazing! The high quality food for the price is what keeps me coming back. I feel like I'm in Mexico on a beach side restaurant. The host and servers are wonderful, they will remember you after next time you visit and you can't say that about too many places. It makes you feel more welcomed than it already is.

The food at this place is on point. It's pretty new but I've already eaten here several times. Everything is very tasty and prepared fresh. It's a la carte style and you are able to try multiple things for a decent price. The owners came and asked our opinion on both visits, which I thought was nice.
I'll definitely be going back. My advice would be to save room for the dulce de Leche crepes.  They are on point.

This restaurant appeared on my radar when I found a Groupon so we decided to visit on a Sunday prior to seeing a show at the Smith Center.  My wife and I ordered a total of 4 tacos, (2) El Fish (shrimp, black beans, avocado and chipolte cream, (1) Al pastor, (fish filet with scallions, onions and grilled pineapple) and (1) poblano (fish filet with poblano rojas, corn and sour cream). While we waited for the tacos to be prepared, our waitress gave us a sample of their fish soup. I was somewhat disappointed in the flavor of the poblano taco, but the 2 other varieties were fresh tasting. We also shared a strawberry crème brulee which was more very soft and bathed in cream.

I am so glad I found this place! I'm not big on seafood in general, but my boyfriend is obsessed, and I DO love a good fish taco. Which, if that's what you are looking for, is one of the highlights of this restaurant.

Even upon first impression, the restaurant is impressive. Whoever decorated did a wonderful job; it reminds me of a little cozy cafe. 

We tried to eat a little of everything but definitely need to make another trip soon. We tried four different tacos - El Fish Taco, Fish and Chips taco, Octopus taco and Baja taco. I tried all except the octopus and they were amazing. The restaurant really uses the seafood flavors to make the food delicious, rather than covering it up with unnecessary spices and such. 

I also tried a carne asada gordita, which was delicious. I only wish it had some cheese sprinkled in it or something extra. My boyfriend also ordered the mixed ceviche, which he proclaimed amazing (and he's picky about these things). I tried to juice part of it with a cracker and it was actually very good. 

Their salsas are also a highlight - delicious and very spicy! And since we were there for lunch our tacos were part of the lunch special and we got some delicious Jamaica (hibiscus juice). 

On top of everything else, we received excellent service. Both servers were so kind, and very prompt with our orders. I will definitely come here again because there are lots of other things I want to try!

In a little locals place in Vegas.
Food is real good.
Great fish soup and good prices.

I don't know how many 5 star ratings I've given..not many I'm sure, this deserves it.. these tacos are the best I've had in vegas..

at first I was skeptical, i ordered two tacos and they put the sauce on the side.. probably because I'm white and the waiter said it was spicy.. he looked really surprised when i asked for more hot sauce.. and to be honest they should never assume because the sauces is what make this place so much better than their competition.. the chipotle sauce they use is too good to even describe.. ask for extra you'll be glad you did.. 

I swear some people rate places five stars because they were starving and they think its the best when really they would say anything was the best... not in my case i went to El pollo loco first.. and as i was leaving was still hungry.. one bite and i immediately regretted el pollo loco.. and i love el pollo!!!
New to the neighborhood - great spot! Tastefully decorated with a unique menu. The chipotle shrimp burrito was fantastic. Friendly staff as well. We'll be back!
Amazingly delicious, fresh from scratch, authentic and affordable, yum! I'll be back again and again...

I wanted to like it but....hmmmm. Maybe I'll try something else before I finish this post
The service is excellent tho
2nd time here, great food, great staff and service. Small dog friendly, possibly any size dog friendly with patio seating
One word. "WOW" definitely coming back. Great service, pleasant atmosphere and amazing tacos.

Great experience!
I took my 3 boys here for dinner last night. We started with some fresh just made chips and guacamole. The guacamole was perfect!
My 2 younger boys opted for the carne asada burritos, my older son and I tried a mix of the different seafood & fish tacos. The fresh homemade corn tortillas rocked! Octopus and fish tacos were beautifully presented and the taste matched.

Service: Junior was outstanding! He was friendly and attentive. 

We will definitely be back!
I highly appreciate this place!! Pricing is reasonable too

I used to love his place was there every single Monday and Thursday now  the food has changed and the service is worst :-/ the tacos are really good a little pricy but good just can't go back it super hot and the waiter manger or owner who ever it was was to
Busy on his laptop and had to ask for our order like 6 times we on order 3 tacos two fish tacos 1 costera taco that's all and had to ask us 6 times for it we ended up leave :-( it's sucks cause I loved it before

So fresh and tasty!  What a nice surprise!  Totally exceeded my expectations.  Used to come by here occasionally for gorditas but noticed the sign changed and really didn't consider trying the new place. What a mistake!  It's now table service with some really unique items, check out the menu.  The fish tacos are not your average fish tacos. They had black beans, rice, avocado and a yummy sauce!  Shrimp on the tostada tasted so clean and fresh not like other shrimp commonly found around town and piled high!  And they have the gorditas on the menu still!  The lunch special was two tacos of your choice and included an agua fresca for $4.99!  Amazing for the quality!  Make it a point to try this place if your in the area.  No beer or wine yet but the staff assured me that is only temporary and they are just waiting to get the official sign off on the liquor license, any day now.  Can't wait to take some friends to this new find in that area.

Really cute set up. Presentation of the food is very cute and elegant. Food is inexpensive and very pleasing. My husband and I were surprised that the food didn't come with guacamole, but it honestly didn't need it. The food was very flavorful. The tacos are small, but it fills you up just right. Will definitely come in more often.
Outdoor seating, friendly owner and staff. We were turned into the Costra, their specialty. Excellent and a Mexican Coke. Solid meal.

This place is really good. They offer a variety of different tacos and other items that I have never even heard of before at other Mexican or fusion places. I had the house el taco costra which is basically a taco with fish...but it also includes a layer of cheese which is grilled forming like a cheese tortilla. The sauce spread over the taco is also really delicious. Also had thr garlic marinated octopus in the light form with lettuce you can also order it prepared in jicama instead of a tortilla. Will be coming back.
Tried surf/turf, lobster and fish. Stellar freshness. Chips/salsa were amazing. Really well done lunch. Loved it.
Loved it, great food decent price! Definitely will be eating here again. Come bring you're friends and family, finger licking good

Ww!  Man am I glad I stopped in here for lunch.  I was actually on my way to another place when I happened to see the big Sign "El Fish Taco" . I have never been here before and we'll I love me some good fish tacos.  I  am in and the atmosphere is very nice and has a beach feel to it. The menu is very simple and to the point. 

After I looked over the menu I decided on the El Fish Taco . Seemed only right. I also order the chips and salsa. The chips ce out and were fresh and hot! Such a nice change from the regular.  When the tacos came I was in awe.  They were hot fresh and best of all so damn good! 

I would highly recommend you try this spot out. I know that I am coming back again there are so many more things I want to just try here. This is definitely a 5 star place. Enjoy!

Well the three amigos had mixed feeling on this fairly new restaurant.  The atmosphere is great, we loved the sea shore motif and the large outdoor patio.
Nearly all of the food here is ala carte. The moment we took a seat the waiter was quick to bring a cup of their seafood broth in this tiny silver cup.  I thought this was kind of odd and felt the soup should have been delivered after we had seen the menu and at least ordered.  Ignacio loved the soup, Uriel and myself both thought it was way to fishy.  Yea, I know its a fish soup.  But while it came with a lime wedge we just did not like the flavor.  We started with the freshly make quac and chips.  It was a nice size for $6 but for us we added more lime and salt.  Ignacio had the gordita plate @ $9 choosing the chicharron and the Rajas gorditas. These were not a hit for him as he said they lacked any flavor at all and the rice an beans that came with it were just mediocre.  Uriel had both the shrimp tostada @ $6 and a carne asada taco at $3.50.  He was more than happy with both and said he would have them again.  I had the shrimp caesar salad @ $11.  This came in a nice large bowl but the salad was mostly the inside lettuce pieces of the romain lettuce.  I pulled out 3 or 4 pieces of core from the salad which just is really not even edible.  The rest were the inside leaves of the romain and not those large green delicious outer leaves.  The shrimp was small and the croutons were plain as was the dressing.
While we had a groupon worth $20 our bill still came to $29 making this meal $49 plus the tip. So this place is somewhat more expensive than your average taco joint.  The owner did bring us a couple items to try because Ignacio did tell him he did not like the gorditas.
I think we will probably try this place again in the future.
Enjoy!
I Love This place! Finally something different not your typical tacos the fusion of flavors is amazing 2 tums!!!

Today's lunch was a pleasant surprise, we happen to be their first customers. The food was very fresh & delicious. We were immediately served, very attentive friendly staff. They have some unique items on the menu and the establishment was tastefully decorated.
It's 7:30pm Saturday... and they are closed! They should update their hours... or continue to waste people's time. How upsetting.

Super nice experience over all, the place really nice,clean, the service really good, she was always checking on us making sure our drinks where always full, but the way the jamaica was delicious it was obviously the real thing not the fake stuff that they always give you other places, I have the chance to try the lobster, shrimp and fish tacos and it was Delicious the fish my favorite,shrimp really good lobster to but a little bit over priced for a person who will eat 5 tacos ( me) lol.... And of course They have a lot more to choose from but definitely is going to be my place to go for fish tacos and real good Jamaica.... Oh and don't forget the dessert you will not be disappointed

Second time I've been here now, and I must say service was slow both times. The server/host/food runner combination really takes away from efficiency in my opinion. However the server is always friendly, despite the lack of expediency at times. 

Moving on from the service, the food is actually a refreshing change of the usual Mexican foods, as you won't find the generic carne asada and such dishes here. Octopus Tostada is one I highly recommend, very nice blend of textures and flavors. Price is also very acceptable for the portion and sizes.

This place is amazing I am so happy to have been introduced to this place. Everything was fresh customer service was amazing and it is very clean!! 

I got the lunch special $4.99 two tacos of your choice a small shrimp soup and a agua fresca either jamaica or horchata it was delicious filling and such a cute presentation!!!

Highly recommend it!!

Well now the make the own rules we been there few times never a problem with the gruponn  now 
They didn't want to take it why the have to be so picky because my date was Latina big BS 
We had a Groupon to spend $40 with 4 guess they never enforce that until today .. we spend over $40 in you over price food no way Jose ...
Off my list.  Over price tacos any ways...
And every thing else..
THIS IS A MEXICAN JOINT IN THE GETTO 
YOUR ARE NOT ON THE STRIP.....
no wonder they have a Groupon deal to get people in....
Super great service and absolutely delicious food. I am impressed and will be returning to explore more of the menu. I am very happy I found this place.

What a great place!  Good service, nice vibe and amazing food.  We had the 'house special' Costra, the octopus taco, the seared ahi tuna tostada, hibiscus water - and finished off with a Nutella crepe.  Everything was first rate, tasty, not too spicy.  I will be back!!!
This place is literally the best!! if you haven't tried it or don't like Mexican food you're definitely missing out. I'll keep coming back to this place
Have been a few times and never disappointed! Great variety and quality of food! Good service as well!
